strings:
<voice_0x01000D84><se_low>Yangus: Hello Brains.
Long time no see.
Back at last, eh?

<voice_0x01000D85><se_def>Brains: Well, well. Look who it is!
You came when I was out, did you Yangus?
I'm sorry I wasn't here.

<voice_0x01000D86><se_def>Brains: But you're back again. So if I'm not mistaken,
you must be in need of some information.
Am I right?

<voice_0x01000D87><se_low>Yangus: Always on the ball, eh, Brains!
We're lookin' for this bloke who looks like a clown. Goes by the name o' Dhoulmagus.

<voice_0x01000D88><se_low>Yangus: He's a slipp'ry customer.
Keeps gettin' away from us.
Have you 'eard anyfin'?

<voice_0x01000D89><se_def>Brains: Yes, I've heard about him.
The criminal responsible for murdering the Abbot of Maella Abbey, no less...
<voice_0x01000D8A><se_def>Brains: My sources report seeing him walking over the surface of the sea toward the western continent.

<voice_0x01000D8B><se_low>Yangus: The western cont'nent?
That's a bit 'azy, innit?
Can't ya be more spific?

<voice_0x01000D8C><se_def>Brains: Sorry, that's all I know.
I wish I could tell you more.

<voice_0x01000D8D><se_low>Yangus: Well if you don't know nuffin' more, Brains,
there ain't nuffin' more to know. We'll 'ave to
go to the western cont'nent ourselves.

<voice_0x01000D8E><se_def>Brains: A fine idea, but aren't you forgetting something?
How do you intend to cross the sea?
<voice_0x01000D8F><se_low>Yangus: ...Eh?
<voice_0x01000D90><se_def>Brains: Monster attacks at sea have been significantly worse recently. All crossings from here and from the northern continent have been cancelled.

<voice_0x01000D91><se_def>Brains: You could go if you had your own ship,
but unless I'm misinformed, you don't.
I'd say that will pose quite a problem.
<voice_0x01000D92><se_low>Yangus: Er...yeah...I 'adn't thought o' that.

<voice_0x01000D93><se_def>Brains: No, I can see that.
Well, perhaps I can help you out there with
a little snippet of information I heard.
<voice_0x01000D94><se_def>Brains: Follow the cliffs along the coast to the west from Port Prospect, and you will come to a wide open wasteland.
<voice_0x01000D95><se_def>Brains: According to what I hear, there's an old, abandoned ship there.

<voice_0x01000D96><se_def>Brains: I don't know why a ship should be in a
place devoid of water, but anyway...
People say it's a magic ship.

<voice_0x01000D97><se_def>Brains: If you could get it up and running again,
you'd be able to sail anywhere you wanted.

<voice_0x01000D98><se_def>Brains: You might want to try the path to the west of Port Prospect. It was blocked by a rockslide,
but I hear that's been cleared up now.
